  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [x] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\n_No response_\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating System\n\nNone\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nThe latest refactor seems to have broken how I consumed forge for an app I am building. \r\n\r\nHow I used it:\r\n- import `foundry-cli`\r\n- parse a Vec<&str> into TestArgs/BuildArgs via clap derive\r\n- invoke `args.run()`\r\n\r\nThat enabled me to easily use forge programmatically, without duplicating any of the helper code (e.g set remappings, etc.)\r\n\r\nCurrently, `TestArgs` lives inside `forge/bin/*`, making consuming it impossible.\r\n\r\nMy question is:\r\n- Should we refactor it again to enable consumption as I did before\r\n- Should I consume `forge` in some other way?",
